[ProMED-mail once again thanks Dr Berger for his background reports.
The coypu or nutria (_Myocastor coypus_) are large, herbivorous,
semiaquatic rodents. Originally native to subtropical and temperate
South America, coypu have since been introduced to North America,
Europe, Asia, and Africa, primarily by fur ranchers
(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coypu). For a picture of coypu, see
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coypu. - Mod.ML]
